sentences: Melodie Crittenden (born 1968 in Shawnee, Oklahoma) is an American country and Christian music artist.

Later in life, she recorded a self-titled debut album for Asylum/Elektra Records in 1998, the same year that she charted with her rendition of "Bless the Broken Road" (her version was titled simply "Broken Road"); she would later record the song a second time as a member of the gospel group Selah.

Crittenden has released two studio albums, starting with her self-titled debut in 1998.
A third album, entitled The Woman I Am, was slated for release around 2004 but was never released.
